1. Nf3 Nf6 {Experts compare Fischer's aggressive, scientific style to that of Russia's famed Alekhine, his flair for combinations to the touch of the U.S. master, Morphy. Amazing all Byrne has to do is take that knight on his 18th move and Game of The Century never happens! It was already 2 years after Donald Byrne defeated Grandmaster Yuri Averbakh in a 4-game match. Byrne played the opening in a very sloppy way. 11. Bg5? it's such an ugly move. It violates two principles: not to move the same piece twice in the opening and king safety, given that the pin in f3 is troublesome for such purposes. The real "Game of the Century" for Bobby Fischer at least, is famous game 1963 with Robert Eugene Byrne. Keep in mind that he was not so lucky in 4 other games in this tournament, which he lost. So his chess abilities were unstable and unpredictable and that's normal in this age. If you check the games of young Magnus Carlsen or Alireza Firouzja, there are a lot of incredible games but also some miserable ones among them.}

